    "question_text": "<h3>Serialize and Deserialize Binary Tree</h3><p>Serialize a binary tree into a string and deserialize it back.</p>",
    "difficulty": "HARD",
    "marks": 15,
    "input_format": "Binary tree (root).",
    "output_format": "Deserialized root.",
    "constraints": [
        "nodes <= 10^4"
    ],
    "explanation": "Use pre-order traversal for serialization, marking null nodes as \"#\". Use a queue for deserialization.",
    "answer": "class Codec:\n    def serialize(self, root):\n        def doit(node):\n            if node: vals.append(str(node.val)); doit(node.left); doit(node.right)\n            else: vals.append(\"#\")\n        vals = []; doit(root); return \",\".join(vals)\n    def deserialize(self, data):\n        def doit():\n            val = next(vals)\n            if val == \"#\": return None\n            node = TreeNode(int(val)); node.left = doit(); node.right = doit(); return node\n        vals = iter(data.split(\",\")); return doit()",
